@owner: TrellisProject
@stability: experimental
@since: 2026-05-09
@reviewed: 2026-05-10
@allow-many-consumes: "workspace loader composes parser + extractor + builder; coupling to those pipeline stages is structural and required for the load pass to be a single transactional operation"

Feature: Workspace Loader
  "Discovers .trellis files under one or more roots, parses each, and assembles the graph."

  Provides:
    - graph.Load
    - graph.LoadResult
    - graph.ParseError

  Consumes:
    - parser.ParseFile
    - graph.Extract
    - graph.Build
    - graph.Graph
    - graph.Sidecar

  Invariants:
    - Load MUST NOT abort on per-file parse failures — failures are returned as ParseErrs alongside the partial graph
    - The walk MUST skip hidden directories (leading '.') below the root, so vendored caches do not dominate large repos
    - The walk SHALL NOT follow symlinks (filepath.WalkDir behavior — preserved deliberately)
    - Returned Sidecars MUST be sorted by absolute path so CLI output and tests are stable
    - File paths in the returned graph SHALL be absolute (post-filepath.Abs)
    - Trees with HasError() true MUST be rejected at load time — Extract is only called on clean trees

  OutOfScope:
    - Source-file pairing verification (the orphaned-source check)
    - .trellisignore / glob exclusion (no real-world need yet)
    - Concurrent / parallel parsing (single-threaded is fast enough for v1)
    - Watch mode / incremental reload

  Scenario (happy-path): Directory walk discovers all .trellis files
    Given a directory tree containing N .trellis files (some nested in subdirectories)
    When Load is called with that root
    Then the graph contains exactly N Sidecars

  Scenario (happy-path): File argument loads exactly one sidecar
    Given a single .trellis file path passed as a root
    When Load is called
    Then the graph contains exactly that one Sidecar

  Scenario (negative): One file fails to parse
    Given a workspace where one .trellis file has a syntax error
    When Load is called
    Then the LoadResult.ParseErrs has one entry naming that file
    And the Graph contains every other file's Sidecar

  Scenario (edge): Hidden directory is skipped
    Given a root containing '.git/something.trellis'
    When Load is called
    Then that file is NOT in the resulting graph

  Scenario (edge): Multiple roots deduplicate
    Given two overlapping roots that both reach the same .trellis file
    When Load is called with both roots
    Then the file appears exactly once in the graph
